# Opioid behavioral modeling

Before editing this folder, read `opioid_behavioral_model/LLM_WIKI.md`.

- v1 is **behavior-only**; no neural fitting unless user provides data.
- Do **not** assume mice represent full PR schedule; use latent engagement state (Models 0–3).
- **Passive group** is not only control — PIT-like withdrawal seeking and patient-relevant transition are core claims.
- Treat `x_t` as hidden value; map to lick rate via softplus/sigmoid (Model 1).
- PR ≠ foraging patch-leave; model continue/pause/quit on one patch.
- JSONL schema: see `Morphine_PR_Experiment_Documentation.md` in parent directory.
